ESP-IDF Component Manager downloads them at build time (`idf.py build`) into
clients/esp32/managed_components/ (a gitignored directory). After building, the
full license text for each lives in its own directory under the path noted below:

- LVGL (lvgl__lvgl) — MIT License.
  https://github.com/lvgl/lvgl
  LVGL itself bundles 25+ libraries (BSD / MIT / Zlib / FreeType / Apache-2.0);
  see managed_components/lvgl__lvgl/COPYRIGHTS.md for the full inventory.

- esp_lvgl_port, esp_lcd_touch, esp_lcd_touch_gt911, esp_websocket_client
  (espressif__*) — Apache License 2.0.
  https://github.com/espressif/idf-extra-components

